{
  "stem": "11272.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I'll just give you a few little incidents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The worst part was when we were sometimes stuck under, you know, bridges, at railroads tracks, on the roads.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we were pleading with the German people and the Polish people to please throw us some snow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because the, the thirst was awful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "People were biting their skins to get a little bit of blood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They didn't have much blood, [LAUGHS] but to get a little bit of wetness on their lips.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "If ice formed on the corner, people were begging, please, pick me up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So even though most of them that did it, their lips froze, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They came down, they had no lips.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the pain was so horrible, people were tearing their own guts out with their fingers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because that thirst pain was just impossible to describe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Hunger pain is bad-- beating pain, broken bones-- but it cannot compare to the thirst pain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And to see, on top of that, ordinary civilian people seeing us dying, pleading for a little snow, which wouldn't cost them nothing-- they didn't do it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They didn't care.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was probably more painful than anything else for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They just said, du bist ein Jude, you're a Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was so disturbing for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It, it was so painful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By the time we arrived in Buchenwald, which was, I don't know, five, six, seven, or eight days later-- I have no idea-- only eight of us were alive, out of the 120 people.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was more dead than alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, I was not with him in the coal car.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But finally, I-- Buchenwald was not designed as an extermination camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when we arrived there, they gave us two slices of real bread.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
